
Basic Syntax
async function functionName() {
  // asynchronous code
}


or arrow function:

const functionName = async () => {
  // async code
};


Key Points

async â†’ makes a function return a Promise
await â†’ pauses execution until Promise resolves
Makes async code look like normal step-by-step code


Simple async function

async function greet() {
  return "Hello";
}
greet().then((msg) => console.log(msg));



example2: 
function waitTwoSeconds() {
  return new Promise((resolve) => {
    setTimeout(() => {
      resolve("Done after 2 seconds");
    }, 2000);
  });
}

async function run() {
  let result = await waitTwoSeconds();
  console.log(result);
}

run();
ðŸ‘‰ Flow:
run() starts
await pauses
2 seconds later Promise resolves
prints result

ðŸ‘‰ An async function is a function that returns a Promise and allows writing asynchronous code using await in a synchronous style.